<TextSection>
  <h3 id="mind-gym">
    <span>1.</span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#"
      >"Mind Gym: An Athlete's Guide to Inner Excellence"</a
    >
    by Gary Mack and David Casstevens
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <BooksQuote
    quote="The difference between a good athlete and a top athlete is that a top athlete has learned to control their fear and use it to their advantage."
  />

  <p class="!mt-6">
    Mind Gym is not your usual self-help book; it's a guide that will change the
    way you think and perceive challenges.
  </p>
  <p>
    The book offers a unique approach to sports psychology, with easy-to-apply
    techniques that can enhance performance, mental toughness, and motivation.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you want to learn how to use your mind to enhance your sports
    performance, <a class="underline link--theme " href="#">Mind Gym</a> is a game-changer.
  </p>
</TextSection>

<TextSection>
  <h3 id="champions-mind">
    <span>2. </span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#"
      >"The Champion's Mind: How Great Athletes Think, Train, and Thrive"</a
    >
    by Jim Afremow
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <BooksQuote
    quote="Every day, remind yourself why you signed up for this journey, and remember the joy and love that inspired you to pursue it."
  />

  <p class="!mt-6">
    The Champion's Mind is a book that offers practical guidance for athletes
    who want to excel in their sport.
  </p>
  <p>
    The book covers essential aspects of sports psychology, such as motivation,
    goal setting, focus, and mental toughness.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you're looking for a step-by-step guide to develop a champion's
    mentality, you should read <a class="underline link--theme " href="#"
      >The Champion's Mind.</a
    >
  </p>
</TextSection>

<TextSection>
  <h3 id="the-art-of-learning">
    <span>3.</span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#"
      >"The Art of Learning: An Inner Journey to Optimal Performance"</a
    >
    by Josh Waitzkin
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <BooksQuote
    quote="Innovation comes from the marriage of the conscious and unconscious mind."
  />

  <p class="!mt-6">
    The Art of Learning is not your usual sports psychology book; it's a memoir
    that takes you on an inner journey to discover your optimal performance.
  </p>
  <p>
    The book shares Waitzkin's personal experience as a world champion chess
    player and martial artist, offering insights on how to apply the principles
    of learning to any field.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you're looking to discover your inner path to success and learn how to
    innovate in your sport, <a class="underline link--theme" href="#"
      >The Art of Learning</a
    > is a must-read.
  </p>
</TextSection>

<TextSection>
  <h3 id="drive">
    <span>4.</span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#"
      >"Drive: The Surprising Truth About What Motivates Us"</a
    >
    by Daniel H. Pink
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <BooksQuote
    quote="The ultimate freedom for creative groups is the freedom to experiment with new ideas. Some skeptics insist that innovation is expensive. In the long run, innovation is cheap."
  />

  <p class="!mt-6">
    Drive is a book that explores the science of motivation and how it affects
    our performance.
  </p>
  <p>
    The book provides a fresh perspective on what drives us, highlighting the
    importance of autonomy, mastery, and purpose.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you're looking for a book that will help you understand what motivates
    you and how to leverage that in your sport, <a
      class="underline link--theme"
      href="#">Drive</a
    > is a must-read.
  </p>
</TextSection>

<TextSection>
  <h3 id="the-talent-code">
    <span>5. </span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#"
      >"The Talent Code: Greatness Isn't Born, It's Grown. Here's How."</a
    >
    by Daniel Coyle
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <BooksQuote
    quote="The sweet spot of challenge is where motivation and learning intersect."
  />

  <p class="!mt-6">
    The Talent Code is a book that challenges the common perception that
    greatness is a natural gift you're born with.
  </p>

  <p>
    The book delves into the neuroscience of learning and talent development,
    highlighting the importance of deep practice, ignition, and master coaching.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you're looking for a book that will change the way you think about talent
    and how to develop it, <a class="underline link--theme" href="#"
      >The Talent Code</a
    > is a must-read.
  </p>
</TextSection>

<TextSection>
  <h3 id="its-not-about-the-bike">
    <span>6.</span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#"
      >"It's Not About the Bike: My Journey Back to Life"</a
    >
    by Lance Armstrong
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <BooksQuote quote="We have only one life, and one chance to make it count." />

  <p class="!mt-6">
    It's Not About the Bike is an inspiring memoir about Lance Armstrong's
    journey back to life after being diagnosed with cancer.
  </p>

  <p>
    The book provides an inside look at Armstrong's personal struggle with
    cancer and how he used his experience to become a seven-time Tour de France
    champion.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you're looking for a book that will inspire you to overcome adversity and
    achieve your dreams, <a class="underline link--theme" href="#"
      >"It's Not About the Bike"</a
    > is a must-read.
  </p>
</TextSection>

<TextSection>
  <h3 id="inner-game-of-tennis">
    <span>7. </span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#"
      >"The Inner Game of Tennis: The Classic Guide to the Mental Side of Peak
      Performance"</a
    >
    by W. Timothy Gallwey
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <BooksQuote
    quote="The mark of a good coach is that, instead of taking players where they want to go, he takes them where they don't necessarily want to go but ought to be."
  />

  <p class="!mt-6">
    The Inner Game of Tennis is a classic sports psychology book that has helped
    athletes worldwide enhance their mental toughness.
  </p>

  <p>
    The book provides a unique approach to sports psychology, focusing on how to
    overcome self-doubt, distractions, and negative thinking.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you're looking for a book that will help you master your inner game and
    develop mental toughness, <a class="underline link--theme" href="#"
      >The Inner Game Of Tennis</a
    > is a must-read.
  </p>
</TextSection>

<TextSection>
  <h3 id="bring-your-a">
    <span>8.</span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#"
      >"Bring Your "A" Game: A Young Athlete’s Guide to Mental Toughness"</a
    >
    by Jennifer L. Etnier
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <BooksQuote
    quote="YOU'VE GOT WHAT IT TAKES, BUT IT WILL TAKE EVERYTHING YOU'VE GOT"
  />

  <p class="!mt-6">
    Are you a young athlete looking to reach your full potential?
  </p>

  <p>
    Look no further than Jennifer L. Etnier's <a
      class="underline link--theme"
      href="#">"Bring Your "A" Game"</a
    >. This book offers key strategies for mental training, such as goal
    setting, pre-performance routines and confidence building. Each of the
    chapters focuses on a particular mental skill with exercises designed to
    help reinforce the concepts so that you can become your best self in sport.
  </p>

  <p>
    Mental training is just as important as physical training when it comes to
    reaching success as an athlete. Allow this book to be your guide and start
    taking charge of all aspects of your performance today — not only will it
    help you succeed but also equip you with knowledge that will stay with you
    long after competition day has ended!
  </p>

  <p>
    Purchase <a class="underline link--theme" href="#">"Bring Your "A" Game"</a>
    now!
  </p>
</TextSection>

<TextSection>
  <h3 id="true-athletic-potential">
    <span>9.</span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#">"Unleash Your True Athletic Potential"</a>
    by Julianne Soviero
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <p class="!mt-6">
    Are you tired of trying to figure out how to become the best athlete you can
    be?
  </p>

  <p>
    Unleash Your True Athletic Potential by Julianne Soviero is the definitive
    guide on becoming a top-tier athlete. It includes advice from some of the
    best coaches, athletes, trainers and physical therapists in the world and
    provides actionable steps for improving your performance. This comprehensive
    resource covers nutrition, sleep, hydration, cross training, injury
    prevention and muscle recovery so that you can maximize your potential as an
    athlete.
  </p>

  <p>
    With this book in your corner, you’ll have all the tools needed to unlock
    that hidden level of success within yourself - no matter if you’re a
    professional or just starting out. Now is your chance to get ahead with
    expert guidance from seasoned professionals! Don’t miss this opportunity!
  </p>

  <p>
    Buy <a class="underline link--theme" href="#"
      >Unleash Your True Athletic Potential</a
    > now and start taking control of your athletic career today!
  </p>
</TextSection>

<TextSection>
  <h3 id="failing-forward">
    <span>10.</span>
    <a class="link--theme" href="#"
      >"Failing Forward: Turning Mistakes into Stepping Stones for Success"</a
    >
    by John C. Maxwell
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard products={1} />
  </div>

  <BooksQuote quote="Fail early, fail often, but always fail forward" />

  <p class="!mt-6">Struggling with the fear of making mistakes?</p>

  <p>
    New York Times best-selling author John C. Maxwell’s book, <a
      class="underline link--theme"
      href="#">Failing Forward</a
    >
    can help you turn your life around and make mistakes work in your favor. It offers
    powerful principles about harnessing failure to fuel success. You’ll learn how
    to view failure as a part of life rather than something to be feared or avoided
    at all costs.
  </p>

  <p>
    This game-changing practical guide will arm you with invaluable lessons on
    turning negative experiences into positive outcomes — so that even if you
    fail, you won't have failed without taking away valuable knowledge along the
    way!
  </p>

  <p>
    Get your copy of John C. Maxwell's <a class="underline link--theme" href="#"
      >Failing Forward</a
    > today and set yourself up for success!
  </p>
</TextSection>
